7 An Act relating to professions and occupations;
amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section 396.2, which relates
8 to definitions; modifying certain terms to include
natural organic reduction; amending 59 O.S. 2021,
9 Section 396.3a, which relates to persons and
businesses required to be licensed; requiring
10 individuals engaged in cremating or natural organic
reduction to be licensed; amending 59 O.S. 2021,
11 Section 396.4, as amended by Section 3, Chapter 381,
O.S.L. 2025 (59 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 396.4),
12 which relates to fees; adding a fee for natural
organic reduction facility license or renewal;
13 amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section 396.12, which relates
to inspection of premises; allowing the Oklahoma
14 Funeral Board to inspect establishments that engage
in organic reduction; amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section
15 396.12c, which relates to revocation or suspension of
licenses; providing for revocation under certain
16 conditions for organic reduction; amending 59 O.S.
2021, Section 396.29, which relates to certain
17 cremation regulations; providing for the same
regulations for organic reduction; amending 59 O.S.
18 2021, Section 396.32, which relates to the residue
from cremated bodies; providing for regulations of
19 residue from organically reduced bodies; amending 59
O.S. 2021, Section 396.33, as amended by Section 534,
20 Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (59 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
396.33), which relates to cremation without license
21 and permit; making organic reduction without license
or permit subject to felony charges; regulating the
22 practice of natural organic reduction; requiring
licensure; requiring record keeping; subjecting
23 natural organic reduction facilities to inspection;
providing for codification; and providing an
24 effective date.
