1 e. is responsible for the legal and ethical operation of
2 a crematory or natural organic reduction facility;
3 3. "Funeral establishment" means a place of business used in
4 the care and preparation for burial, commercial embalming, or
5 transportation of dead human remains, or any place where any person
6 or persons shall hold forth and be engaged in the profession of
7 undertaking or funeral directing;
8 4. "Apprentice" means a person who is engaged in learning the
